only when compiled as <br />a module. That's against the ideas of modules - I much prefer it if all <br />the drivers are the same regardless of whether they are compiled as <br />modules or not (that way there are no surprises).<br /><br />pre-2.0.6 should have the dummy driver working again, as well as the <br />alias setup. Addign an open routine for alias makes sense anyway, in case <br />we ever want to have that as a module in which case the open routine is <br />needed for reference counting.<br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
